rComments: Somewhat of a dry lecturer; doesn't add anything new to her slides and just reads whats there for the most part. But because the course material is very interesting you don't really mind it. She's very unclear in terms of her expectations. Midterm and final were very fair but you absolutely need to study the textbook. She shows videos--go to class.

She's really down to earth. Great Speaker and friendly. She's engaging and understanding. Presents the content in an interesting way. I really did have great respect for her. If you're taking Social Motivation, I recommend you take it with her.  25% of your grade are just 1 page diary entries! (Boosters). Down side: 45% Exam :(
